There are many differences between String and StringBuffer. A list of differences between String and StringBuffer are given below:

No.	String	                                                                StringBuffer

1)	String class is immutable.	                                StringBuffer class is mutable.

2)	String is slow and consumes                                 StringBuffer is fast and consumes less memory when you cancat strings.
more memory when you concat too many strings
because every time it creates new instance.

3)	String class overrides the equals() method                  StringBuffer class doesn't override the equals() method of Object class.
of Object class. So you can compare the contents
of two strings by equals() method.
